            It is
strange that so many of those most offended by globalization call themselves
"progressives." <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Early this century</TIMEX>, the progressives were <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX> who realized
that communications and transportation technologies were pushing the scope of
economic activity outward, from individual <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">states</ENAMEX> to the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">United States</ENAMEX> as a
whole. They responded by pushing economic regulation from the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">state</ENAMEX> to the
